    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>High government officers appointed by or under the authority of a sovereign or head of government, usually holding a position of authority in a particular administrative department or other division of government activity.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Altos funcionarios de gobierno decretado por o bajo la autoridad de un soberano o el dirigiente de un gobierno, usualmente poseen una posición de autoridad en un departamento administrativo particular u otra división de la actividad gubernamental.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
